column1: Estimates generated by the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (IGME) in 2015
Note: Lower, Median and Upper refer to the lower bound, median and upper bound of 90% uncertainty intervals.

The P factor represents the expected to estimated female mortality rate, in more detail estimated sex ratio/expected sex ratio, where estimated sex ratio = estimated male mortality/estimated female mortality; expected sex ratio = estimated male mortality/expected female mortality.
